StringWithMarkup.String: Antimony trichloride is a colorless crystalline solid. It is shipped as a solid or liquid solution. It is decomposed slowly by water to hydrochloric acid and antimony oxychloride. Antimony oxychloride is soluble in hydrochloric acid but insoluble in water. It is corrosive to metals and tissue.
COLOURLESS HYGROSCOPIC CRYSTALS WITH PUNGENT ODOUR.
